private/

# docs/ holds both private analysis (e.g. ecosystem notes) and the
# public per-section documentation split out of the main README. Default
# is to ignore everything in docs/, then explicitly negate the user-facing
# files. (Negation only works because the pattern is `docs/*` not `docs/` —
# git can't re-include a file under an excluded directory.)
docs/*
!docs/getting-started.md
!docs/tools.md
!docs/workflows.md
!docs/prompts.md
!docs/http-mode.md
!docs/migrating.md
!docs/cedar-primer.md
!docs/troubleshooting.md

*.private.md
*.scratch.md
kickoff-*.md
spike-report-*.md

# Anything that could leak from ~/Documents/danit-context/ by accident
danit-context/
internal-docs/

